args:
When Mascula sacrifices his heart to stop
Laxi's rampage, he ceases to function.
Afterward, the prince offers his hand in
friendship. Laxi tries to forestall the decision,
but Mascula's heart within her gives ready
consent to a continuing relationship.
Laxi's stopped! Now is my time to act!
You can't mean to attack her, Mascula.\nThat would go against all that you are!
Right, there's no need for that.\nIt's not my strength that will\nstop her, but my heart!
LAXI! I GIVE YOU MY HEART!\nGRAAAAAAAAGH!
He's tearing something from his body!

This is the apparatus by which
I may judge good and evil.
The one Maestro gifted me.
It is...my heart.
I'm sorry, Luca.\nThis is the only choice.
Laxi's rampage is a result of her\nmalfunctioning heart. If I grant her a\nworking one, the violence will cease.
If we stop Laxi, we stop every android.
This is the best way to ensure\nno one else has to be hurt.
I mean, you're going to lose your HEART!\nWhat even happens to you at that point?
Don't worry. I won't go berserk like Laxi.\nAs my heart also serves as my core, I will\ncease functioning once it is gone.
That AIN'T any better, Mascula! Rrrrrr!\nYou may have a big heart, but you don't\nunderstand a damn thing about mine!
I...I don't want ya to go, all right?!
I'm sorry, Luca. I truly am.
But I have made my decision.\nI am going to fight—for everyone.
I will fight to protect what is important to\nme, just like all of you.
And this is the best way for me to do so!
He...he did it. He actually\nput his heart into Laxi.
That should do it. Once I cease to function,\nmy heart will activate inside Laxi.
Hmm... You could call it that.
I'm sorry we got you and the other\nandroids caught up in our fight, Mascula.
It's because of us that you're going to—
Do not apologize. We androids were\ncreated to fight. It may be our destiny\nto awaken in times of strife.
And in a world beset by war, there was\nsimply no place for a pacifist like me.
Then I'll MAKE a place for ya!
I'll make a world where folks\nlike you aren't forced to fight!
Just hold on, Mascula! Gimme time!\nI promise I'll make it happen!
I am happy to hear that...\nBut time...is something I no longer have.
Affirmative. My designation is Laxi.\nI am the android commander.
Look, I know you've been through a lot,\nbut could I maybe ask you to... Um...
I know what you require. I have already\nchanged the status of all androids from\nactive operation to standby mode.
Thank you. That should help the soldiers\nwho are still fighting on the other front.
Your thanks are unnecessary.\nI am responsible for needless combat,\ntherefore I must rectify the situation.
Yes, how should I put it...?
We were just thinking about how different\nyou are from Mascula.
Mascula is the fail-safe. He is the end.\nHe is the one who eliminates all conflict.
I am his opposite—I initiate conflict.\nI make my fellow androids fight.\nOur essential qualities differ. That is all.
I see. Er, so what will you and all\nof your fellow androids do now?
We will seek that which Maestro sought.\nThat is my purpose now.
A world without conflict.\nA world of peace.
You are not unlike Mascula in that regard.
If that's your ultimate goal,\nwhy don't you come with us?
So we can take you to a world\nwithout conflict or strife.

Your proposal makes no sense.
You and your people are engaged in war. 
If we travel together, I would become
embroiled in this conflict.
I know. That's why we'll protect you.
Incomprehensible. \nAndroids need no protection.\nWe have the power to fight.
Right, but having the power to fight and\nNEEDING to fight are two different things.\nI don't want you to be forced to fight.
To what end would you have us come with\nyou, then? What advantage is there in it?
So you can finally experience peace.
He wanted us to experience peace,\ndespite being born into a world of\nconstant war and strife.
However, I will withhold judgment as to\nwhether you are the same as Maestro.\n▷No, take us with you.◁
Error. There is a glitch in my linguistic\nfaculties. Those were not my words.\n▷Let's go with them, Laxi.◁
I am...very confused right now.\nIt is as if two people are talking at once.

There are excess thoughts within me.
▷Not EXCESS thoughts.
Important ones.◁
Shut up.
It is likely that Mascula's heart merged\nwith my own and caused this glitch.\n▷Laxi, listen to me!◁
▷Think of these people as Maestro. \nLike him, they can help teach us\nhow to live.◁
Your heart has judged this to be so?\n▷Yes. We can trust them.◁
▷Yes, Luca. It is. And now I can see for\nmyself the place you would make for us.◁
Right on! That's what I promised,\nand that's what I'm gonna deliver!
Stop. I am Laxi. I do not care for being\nreferred to by a different designation.
Sorry! Couldn't help it. Anyway,\nnice to have you aboard, MascuLaxi!
Chelle, it would ap-purr the androids have\nfallen into the hands of the seventh heir.
Eee hee hee hee! Oh, what a lovely\ndance that was, Emile.
He danced into the palm of your hand,\njust as you expurr-cted.
However, the androids have now bolstered\nthe military might of New Alberia. This is\na dangerous game you play, purr-incess.

Oh, it's fine! Even with reinforcements,
they're still no match for the Other.
They'll need to build up their strength
even more for that to happen.
I need those twins to play with each other\nfor a while longer.
When the time comes, I'll have them leave\nthe stage.
Meowr hawr hawr! Always so confident.\nDon't blame me if the Empress finds out\nabout this.
But goodness, I am the VICTIM here!\nEmile is the one who took the androids\nand immediately lost them to the enemy.
Mmm, purr-haps. Still, didn't this gambit\ncarry rather unfavorable odds for you?
A lady is modest and graceful,\nbut at times, she must be bold.
It is because we overcome great obstacles\nthat the fires of love are stoked, mmm?
And so once again someone will be\nburned by your flame.
Leonidas will be up next, won't he?\nI hear he's been mobilizing his forces.

My, but your ears hear everything!
That being said, my dear brother's flame
is more the rough, conquering type
than my own delicate fire.
Is it not a fool's errand to pit one flame\nagainst another to see which burns hotter?
Why, join hands and hold a passionate,\nwild, and brilliant PARTY, of course!
Oh, it will be SO grand.\nIsn't that right...Leonidas?
